{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.36",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 36,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 36 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:1",
      "text": "Have mercy upon us, O God of all, and behold us, and shew us the light of thy mercies:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:2",
      "text": "And send thy fear upon the nations, that have not sought after thee: that they may know that there is no God beside thee, and that they may shew forth thy wonders.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:3",
      "text": "Lift up thy hand over the strange nations, that they may see thy power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:4",
      "text": "For as thou hast been sanctified in us in their sight, so thou shalt be magnified among them in our presence,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:5",
      "text": "That they may know thee, as we also have known thee, that there is no God beside thee, O Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:6",
      "text": "Renew thy signs, and work new miracles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:7",
      "text": "Glorify thy hand, and thy right arm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:8",
      "text": "Raise up indignation, and pour out wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:9",
      "text": "Take away the adversary, and crush the enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:10",
      "text": "Hasten the time, and remember the end, that they may declare thy wonderful works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:11",
      "text": "Let him that escapeth be consumed by the rage of the fire: and let them perish that oppress thy people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:12",
      "text": "Crush the head of the princes of the enemies that say: There is no other beside us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:13",
      "text": "Gather together all the tribes of Jacob: that they may know that there no God besides thee, and may declare thy great works: and thou shalt inherit them as from the beginning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:14",
      "text": "Have mercy on thy people, upon whom thy name is invoked: and upon Israel, whom thou hast raised up to be thy firstborn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:15",
      "text": "Have mercy on Jerusalem, the city which thou hast sanctified, the city of thy rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:16",
      "text": "Fill Sion with thy unspeakable words, and thy people with thy glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:17",
      "text": "Give testimony to them that are thy creatures from the beginning, and raise up the prophecies which the former prophets spoke in thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:18",
      "text": "Reward them that patiently wait for thee, that thy prophets may be found faithful: and hear the prayers of thy servants,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:19",
      "text": "According to the blessing of Aaron over thy people, and direct us into the way of justice, and let all know that dwell upon the earth, that thou art God the beholder of all ages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:20",
      "text": "The belly will devour all meat, yet one is better than another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:21",
      "text": "The palate tasteth venison and the wise heart false speeches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:22",
      "text": "A perverse heart will cause grief, and a man of experience will resist it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:23",
      "text": "A woman will receive every man: yet one daughter is better than another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:24",
      "text": "The beauty of a woman cheereth the countenance of her husband, and a man desireth nothing more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:25",
      "text": "If she have a tongue that can cure, and likewise mitigate and shew mercy: her husband is not like other men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:26",
      "text": "He that possesseth a good wife, beginneth a possession: she is a help like to himself, and a pillar of rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:27",
      "text": "Where there is no hedge, the possession shall be spoiled: and where there is no wife, he mourneth that is in want.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.36.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:28",
      "text": "Who will trust him that hath no rest, and that lodgeth wheresoever the night taketh him, as a robber well appointed, that skippeth from city to city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
